Once we get the Supabase CLI working properly, we can start developing our first edge function, I am thinking something to scrape my latest Mastodon posts and put them into my `textposts` table

Heres a fun tip: if you `brew install supabase` and then run `supabase start` it will give you an error like `Cannot connect to the Docker daemon at unix:///var/run/docker.sock. Is the docker daemon running?` - the answer is, no it is not. So you need to `brew install --cask docker` and then open up the Docker app and start it. Couldnt find that documented anywhere, even though it is extremely logical
